    "subtitle": "Danish peptide platform (Soborg; Nasdaq Copenhagen). FOUR-ASSET CARDIOMETABOLIC + RARE DISEASE PIPELINE: (1) PETRELINTIDE (ZP8396, long-acting amylin analog SC weekly) -- Roche partnership Mar 12 2025 ($1.65B up = $1.4B closing + $250M anniversary + up to $1.2B dev milestones + sales/commercial milestones; total ~$5.3B; co-develop+co-commercialize global; includes fixed-dose combo with Roche CT-388 incretin). ZUPREME-1 Ph2 readout Mar 5 2026: 10.7% mean weight loss at 42 wks vs 1.7% placebo (efficacy estimand) -- below high-end consensus. ZUPREME-2 Ph2 obesity+T2D 28wk topline H2 2026. PHASE 3 INITIATING H2 2026 (triggers $575M Roche milestone). (2) SURVODUTIDE (BI 456906, GLP-1/glucagon dual agonist) -- BI partnership; mid-to-low-double-digit royalties. SYNCHRONIZE-1 Ph3 obesity POSITIVE Apr 28 2026: 16.6% weight loss at 76 wks vs 3.2% placebo; 85.1% achieved >=5%. ADA Jun 2026 full data. MASH Ph3 LIVERAGE + LIVERAGE-Cirrhosis ongoing (FDA Breakthrough Therapy). (3) DASIGLUCAGON (Zegalogue) severe hypoglycemia -- out-licensed Novo Nordisk Sept 2022 (DKK 265M milestones + HSD-LDD royalties; Q1 25 royalty DKK 7.7M; weak commercial). Plus FDA priority review for congenital hyperinsulinism (separate; Zealand-led). (4) GLEPAGLUTIDE long-acting GLP-2 SBS -- FDA CRL Dec 19 2024 (insufficient evidence at marketed dose); EASE-5 Ph3 confirmatory H2 2025+ for re-file; EU MAA submitted Jun 2 2025. Cash DKK ~16.6B post-Roche; 2026 OpEx guide DKK 2.7-3.3B; $700M potential 2026 Roche milestones ($575M Ph3 init + $125M anniversary).",
